---
import MainLayout from '../layouts/MainLayout.astro';
---

<MainLayout title="Privacy Policy - QuickQR">
  <div class="legal-container">
    <div class="legal-content">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="last-updated">Last updated: April 6, 2026</p>

      <section>
        <h2>What We Collect</h2>
        <p>We only collect what's necessary to run QuickQR:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account info:</strong> Email address (for login) and any profile details you choose to add</li>
          <li><strong>QR codes:</strong> The content you create (URLs, contact info, etc.) and their styling preferences</li>
          <li><strong>Analytics:</strong> For dynamic QR codes only - we log scan counts, device type (iOS/Android/etc.), and rough location (country/city level)</li>
          <li><strong>Payment info:</strong> Handled by Stripe - we never see your full card details</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>What We Don't Do</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>We don't sell your data to anyone</li>
          <li>We don't track you across the web</li>
          <li>We don't use cookies for advertising</li>
          <li>We don't store passwords in plain text (bcrypt hashed)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>How We Use Your Data</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To display your QR codes and their analytics</li>
          <li>To send you important account notifications</li>
          <li>To prevent abuse and spam (we check for malicious URLs)</li>
          <li>To improve the service (aggregated usage stats, not individual tracking)</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Data Storage</h2>
        <p>Everything lives on Supabase infrastructure (US-based). We keep your QR codes until you delete them or close your account. Backups are retained for 30 days then purged.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>You can:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Export your QR codes anytime</li>
          <li>Delete individual QR codes or your entire account</li>
          <li>Request a copy of your data</li>
          <li>Update your email or profile info</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Email <a href="mailto:support@quickqr.app">support@quickqr.app</a> for data requests.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Static vs Dynamic QR Codes</h2>
        <p><strong>Static QR codes:</strong> We generate the image and that's it. No tracking, no storage of scan data.</p>
        <p><strong>Dynamic QR codes:</strong> We host a redirect and log basic analytics (device type, location, timestamp) so you can see how they're performing.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Security</h2>
        <p>We use industry standard practices: HTTPS everywhere, hashed passwords, row-level security on the database, and regular dependency updates. That said, no system is perfect - don't use QuickQR for nuclear launch codes.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>If we materially change this policy, we'll email you and post a notice. Continued use after changes means you're cool with it.</p>
      </section>

      <section>
        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>Questions? <a href="mailto:support@quickqr.app">support@quickqr.app</a></p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</MainLayout>

<style>
  .legal-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content h1 {
    font-size: 2rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-gray-900, #111827);
    margin: 0 0 0.5rem 0;
  }

  .last-updated {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-gray-500, #6b7280);
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .legal-content section {
    margin-bottom: 2rem;
  }

  .legal-content h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--color-gray-900, #111827);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--color-gray-200, #e5e7eb);
  }

  .legal-content p {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-gray-600, #4b5563);
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
  }

  .legal-content ul {
    margin: 0 0 1rem 0;
    padding-left: 1.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content li {
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    line-height: 1.7;
    color: var(--color-gray-600, #4b5563);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .legal-content a {
    color: var(--color-teal-600, #0d9488);
    text-decoration: none;
  }

  .legal-content a:hover {
    text-decoration: underline;
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .legal-container {
      padding: 2rem 1rem;
    }

    .legal-content h1 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
    }

    .legal-content h2 {
      font-size: 1.125rem;
    }
  }
</style>